# Handled Home — PRD: Provider Onboarding (Mobile-First) + Founding Partner Intake + Agreement Acceptance
**Sprint Name:** Provider Onboarding (Round 3 — next sprint)  
**Launch State:** California-first  
**Users:** Providers (individual + provider org), Ops/Admin, (later) Compliance/Support  
**Purpose:** Funnel *every* provider through a standardized onboarding + eligibility + quality gate, while pitching the right opportunity message based on zone/category market state.

---

## 0) Executive Summary

Provider onboarding is a **mobile-first acquisition and compliance funnel** that:
1) Markets the *right* opportunity (“Founding Partner” vs “Growing Fast” vs “Early Waitlist”) based on zone/category state  
2) Collects the minimum required business info (identity, service categories, coverage, availability, BYOC potential)  
3) Collects and verifies compliance signals (license/insurance where relevant, W-9, etc.)  
4) Captures explicit acceptance of a **Founding Partner Agreement** clause-by-clause  
5) Sends the provider into an **Ops Review Queue** (manual approval initially), with a future path toward automated approvals.

The onboarding should maximize conversion while preserving the platform’s core promise: **Your home is handled** (quality + proof + standards + reliability).

---

## 1) Goals

### 1.1 Growth goals (provider supply)
- Get qualified providers to **download the app**, self-identify category + zone, and apply.
- Enable **BYOC** migration as a primary “zone-entry starter motor.”
- Create “first-mover advantage” urgency without sounding scammy.

### 1.2 Quality + operational goals
- Enforce non-negotiables: **SKUs + Levels + Proof + No Side Deals**
- Collect enough data to avoid onboarding providers who will create support issues.
- Ensure every provider is trackable and accountable (identity, business entity, payout setup, agreement acceptance).

### 1.3 Compliance goals (California launch)
- Capture and store relevant signals for California service work:
  - Contractors State License Board (CSLB) license where applicable
  - Insurance where applicable
  - Bond signals where applicable (contractors bond amounts exist; see CSLB info) :contentReference[oaicite:0]{index=0}
- Provide a framework for “Category Compliance Requirements” so you can add other states later.

> Note: Handled Home should not provide legal advice; the system should implement “requirements by category” and route uncertain cases to Ops review.

---

## 2) Non-goals (v1)
- Fully automated approval without ops involvement
- Real-time verification integrations for every insurance carrier
- Complex commission structures beyond BYOC + founding partner bonus
- Multi-language onboarding (can be later)

