## 4) High-Level UX Flow (Provider App)

### 4.1 Entry: Provider self-identification
On first open / role selection:
- “I’m a customer” / “I’m a provider”
If provider:
- Select: primary categories (multi-select)
- Enter: ZIP code(s) served (or choose zone if you already map)
- Optional: “I already have customers in this area” toggle

### 4.2 Dynamic Opportunity Banner (driven by market state)
Immediately show one of these “Good News!” banners:

**A) Founding Partner / Early Market**
> “Good news — we’re launching in your area soon. We’re offering Founding Partner programs to qualified providers. Apply now to get early priority and BYOC incentives.”

**B) Open / Growing Market**
> “Good news — we’re growing fast in your area. We’re looking for quality providers like you. Apply now to get steady work and optimized routes.”

**C) You’re early, but categories still needed**
> “Good news — you’re one of the first in your area. Apply now. Once we fill a few more categories, Founding Partner spots will be awarded first-come, first-approved.”

**D) Waitlist**
> “We’re not live in your area yet — but you can apply now. We’ll review your application and contact you as soon as your zone opens.”

**E) Closed**
> “We’re currently full in your area. Join the provider waitlist and we’ll notify you when openings appear.”

### 4.3 Application CTA
- “Apply Now” button → enters onboarding wizard

